# API Test Scenarios

This file contains example HTTP requests to test the evolving API version system.
You can use tools like curl, httpie, or REST Client VS Code extension.

## Setup

Start the server:
```bash
npm run dev
```

The server runs on `http://localhost:3000`

---

## Home/Documentation

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000
```

---

## Client Registration

### Register a V1 Client
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"clientId": "my-v1-client", "version": "v1"}'
```

### Register a V2 Client
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"clientId": "my-v2-client", "version": "v2"}'
```

### Register a V3 Client
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"clientId": "my-v3-client", "version": "v3"}'
```

### List All Clients
```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/clients
```

### Update Client Version (Migration)
```bash
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/api/clients/my-v1-client/version \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"version": "v2"}'
```

---

## Task Operations with Different Versions

### Scenario 1: V1 Client (Boolean Completion)

#### List tasks as V1 client (using registered client ID)
```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-Client-Id: client-v1-demo"
```

#### List tasks as V1 client (using version header)
```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v1"
```

#### Create task as V1 client (with completed field)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v1" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title": "Learn API versioning", "completed": false}'
```

#### Update task as V1 client
```bash
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-1 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v1" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"completed": true}'
```

---

### Scenario 2: V2 Client (Status Enum)

#### List tasks as V2 client
```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-Client-Id: client-v2-demo"
```

#### Create task as V2 client (with status enum)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v2" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "title": "Build feature X",
    "status": "in_progress",
    "dueDate": "2026-03-01T00:00:00.000Z"
  }'
```

#### Update task as V2 client
```bash
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-2 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v2" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"status": "done"}'
```

---

### Scenario 3: V3 Client (Priority & Tags)

#### List tasks as V3 client
```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v3"
```

#### Create task as V3 client (with priority and tags)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v3" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "title": "Critical bug fix",
    "status": "todo",
    "dueDate": "2026-02-18T00:00:00.000Z",
    "priority": 5,
    "tags": ["bug", "urgent", "production"]
  }'
```

#### Update task as V3 client
```bash
curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-3 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v3" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "status": "in_progress",
    "priority": 4,
    "tags": ["bug", "urgent", "in-review"]
  }'
```

---

### Scenario 4: Cross-Version Compatibility

#### V1 client creates task, V2 client reads it
```bash
# V1 creates with completed=false
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v1" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title": "Cross-version task", "completed": false}'

# Note the task ID returned (e.g., task-4)

# V2 reads same task - sees status="todo"
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-4 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v2"

# V3 reads same task - sees status="todo", priority=3, tags=[]
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-4 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v3"
```

#### V3 client creates task, V1 client reads it
```bash
# V3 creates with full metadata
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-API-Version: v3" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "title": "Rich task",
    "status": "done",
    "priority": 5,
    "tags": ["important"]
  }'

# Note the task ID returned (e.g., task-5)

# V1 reads same task - sees completed=true (priority/tags stripped)
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-5 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v1"

# V2 reads same task - sees status="done" (priority/tags stripped)
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-5 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v2"
```

---

### Scenario 5: Task Deletion

```bash
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/tasks/task-1 \
  -H "X-API-Version: v1"
```

---

## Testing Version Detection Priority

### Explicit header overrides client registration
```bash
# Register as v1 client
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"clientId": "test-client", "version": "v1"}'

# Use client ID but override with v3 version
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks \
  -H "X-Client-Id: test-client" \
  -H "X-API-Version: v3"
  
# Should return v3 format (with priority and tags)
```

---

## Expected Transformations

### V1 ↔ V2 ↔ V3

**V1 Task:**
```json
{
  "id": "task-1",
  "title": "Example",
  "completed": false,
  "createdAt": "2026-02-16T10:00:00.000Z"
}
```

**Same task in V2:**
```json
{
  "id": "task-1",
  "title": "Example",
  "status": "todo",
  "dueDate": null,
  "createdAt": "2026-02-16T10:00:00.000Z"
}
```

**Same task in V3:**
```json
{
  "id": "task-1",
  "title": "Example",
  "status": "todo",
  "dueDate": null,
  "priority": 3,
  "tags": [],
  "createdAt": "2026-02-16T10:00:00.000Z"
}
```

---

## Quick Test Suite

Run these commands in sequence to verify the system:

```bash
# 1. Register test clients
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"clientId": "test-v1", "version": "v1"}'
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"clientId": "test-v2", "version": "v2"}'
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/clients/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"clientId": "test-v3", "version": "v3"}'

# 2. Create task as V3 (with all fields)
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tasks -H "X-API-Version: v3" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title": "Test Task", "status": "done", "priority": 5, "tags": ["test"]}'

# 3. Read as V1 (should show completed=true)
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks -H "X-API-Version: v1"

# 4. Read as V2 (should show status="done", no priority/tags)
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks -H "X-API-Version: v2"

# 5. Read as V3 (should show full details)
curl http://localhost:3000/api/tasks -H "X-API-Version: v3"
```
